        "timestamp": "2019-03-11 10:05:57.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Marios, I think rather that being a swagger file, this generation is really the definition of the \"inputs\" object. As per https://apihandyman.io/writing-openapi-swagger-specification-tutorial-part-8-splitting-specification-file/ where in the example, the Person definition is placed in a separate, Person.yaml  , we can place the Inputs as a definition in its own Inputs.json file. You see we cannot say this is a swagger or openapi 2.0 specification, as we don't have any paths etc. So maybe just create the Inputs Definition file is the best option ( basically the JSON Schema of the Inputs object ) which is what you have any, so just remove the \"title\", \"swagger\" and \"defintions\" from the JSON generation and you are done",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
